# 8. Clinical Interpretation

The identified candidate variant should be evaluated together with:

- Patient phenotype
- OMIM disease association
- Population allele frequency
- ACMG guidelines
- Published literature

Clinical interpretation should always be confirmed by qualified clinical geneticists before diagnosis.

---

# 9. Conclusion

This project demonstrates a complete Trio Whole Exome Sequencing workflow for identifying candidate de novo variants in a simulated rare disease patient. The pipeline integrates multiple widely used bioinformatics tools to produce clinically relevant candidate variants.

Trio-based sequencing significantly improves diagnostic accuracy by distinguishing inherited variants from newly occurring mutations. The workflow presented in this project provides a strong foundation for rare disease genomics and clinical bioinformatics applications.

